##People from outside Wuhan who deliver drugs to people infected with AIDS

Gayspot

Feature Introduction, Independent magazine, focus on the existence and survival of sexual minorities.

February 8, Lantern Festival. The traditional Lunar New Year holiday is coming to an end on the day when the family and Tangyuan, a symbol of Reunion, eat a meal together. But failed to return home in Zhejiang, stay in Wuhan statement, looked out the window of the weather, clouds layer upon layer, the sun occasionally shed some sunlight. After getting up, he listened to the news, while preparing to personally make some dumplings, is also a person over the festival.

The original plan stated that in the afternoon to send a friend (AIDS virus infection, the following same) to Caidian District Wuhan gold and Silver Lake Hospital to collect medicine. The city has been sealed for 17 days, no one can adapt to once noisy, shouting, noisy Wuhan become quiet, empty, lost fireworks. And the outbreak shows no sign of being contained.

Watching the pot of water gradually boiling, the phone suddenly rang, and another two friends want to go in the morning to pick up medicine, community organization staff asked if it is convenient to go out to pick up now.

Statement calculated the time, now go out, from their residential community to a friend's community, then to the gold and silver pond hospital, and back, basically need to go to pick up the appointment in the afternoon that a friend. "It would be nice to save the mask and just shower once at home, which would be easier. "

The statement responded to the message, turned off the fire, and began dressing, wearing protective clothing, and wearing a mask. And Tangyuan, come back later. Perhaps eating dumplings, you can also video-chat with your parents in Zhejiang, "they didn't approve of me staying in Wuhan at first. "

Not Going home for Chinese New Year

One month in advance, Shen had booked a flight back to Zhejiang on the afternoon of January 22. For the second time in a year and a half in Wuhan, he is preparing to return to his rural hometown in Zhejiang Province with Wuhan specialties. My parents, who always like sweet food, occasionally eat some hot food from Wuhan. They think it is very fresh and interesting.

On January 20, the statement, who was packing, received a message from her prospective boyfriend, "how are you these two days? " The statement was stunned. The last time they saw each other was two days ago, when they went for a walk along the Yangtze River. The two people contact for more than three months, each other has good feelings, is just waiting for a suitable time to determine the relationship.

Before the statement could be answered, the man-to-be sent another message: "My father has basically been diagnosed. My mother and I also have a fever. We are going to the hospital now. If there is a bed, we will be hospitalized. " In a few minutes, for the record, it's like being told to get tested soon after a high-risk sexual encounter a long time ago.

Since January 20, more and more people in the city of Wuhan have shown signs of fever. Between the people of the Marketing buzz, this time the pneumonia is raging. Though he said he did not know at the time that the outbreak was being called COVID-19 pneumonia, his immediate concern was that he needed to be diagnosed quickly in order to decide whether to go home.

21 January. "I didn't dare go to a hospital in the city, " he said at the time, not sure how to better protect himself, "I chose the Golden Pool Hospital, which is not located in the city. It was more than half an hour's drive away. After a check-up, the doctor thought I had no infection and advised me to observe at home. " Fortunately, to this day, the statement states that there is no sign of infection.

Affirming that growing up in a village with a strong focus on tradition and family reunion, not going home for the new year, is almost tantamount to treason and heresy. On the night of January 21st, he didn't sleep well. To others, it was just not going home for the New Year. For him, it was a revolt against his parents, "They don't know I'm gay yet, and even if I don't come out, I may face not getting married or not coming home for more Chinese New Year, " she said.

The soon-to-be-30-year-old did not return home on the grounds that he might catch new pneumonia, and his family gave their consent.

On the 22nd, when he returned his ticket, he did something he would never have done before: he went to the temple to pray for his future boyfriend and his family, hoping they would get well soon.

And that doesn't seem to be enough. On January 25, Shen signed up to be a caring volunteer driver who picked up and dropped off a friend. "because I was lucky, right? The day I signed up, I saw the owner of the small supermarket in the neighborhood post a friend circle, saying he still had masks, and I immediately went to buy 20. " He thought he was ready.

Are you infected, too?

After January 20, the weather in Wuhan was cloudy and rainy, which made many people feel even more depressed. More and more health care workers from all over the country have traveled to Wuhan, constantly joining in the fight against the epidemic, declaring that his parents in his hometown in Zhejiang are in daily contact with him, and from time to time complaining about why he stayed in Wuhan.

While claiming to be under pressure, the first pick-up and drop-off of a friend's task came. What is even more unexpected is that in the coming week, it will drive nearly 500 kilometers, which is almost the number of kilometers driven in the usual two months, "If not for the closure of the city, the traffic in Wuhan would actually be very bad, with frequent traffic jams, " said Shen, who commutes to work by public transport every day and only occasionally drives to the outskirts of the city to climb mountains on weekends.

The first is from Shanghai, the last stop on his long trip to Wuhan, and he plans to return to Shanghai on the afternoon of January 23. The city of Wuhan was closed and he was forced to stay.

"If they go off the drugs again, it means they face a second injury. " This is a statement about the withdrawal of drugs, which may not be accurate enough, but he felt their fear, their anxiety, their panic.

It was the first time that he drove a friend to Wuhan AIDS hospital, Golden Lake Hospital to pick up the drug. He didn't have a hazmat suit, and the only thing he had to protect himself was a mask.

Although this is the first time that a friend from Shanghai has picked up medicine in another place, after making a lot of phone calls, he also finished the preparation work ahead of time, got guidance from the Wuhan Comrade Center, and further contacted the doctors at Jinyintan Hospital. This has become a preparatory process for almost every a friend who has taken the medicine in another place.

A friend was already standing by the side of the road when the car arrived at the designated place. He declared that he was wearing three masks that day, which later hurt him a little, because masks are precious protective equipment. During those two days, it was stated that it would roll down the driver's window, turn off the air-conditioning, and let the air circulate to reduce the probability of infection.

Statement to the hospital only to find that the AIDS clinic and fever clinic is not together, but alone at the end of the corridor, not even through fever clinic.

On January 26 and 27, the weather in Wuhan was still overcast, with occasional drizzle. Staff at the center sent him protective clothing, face masks and other supplies after learning of the statement.

From the second pick up a friend to go to the gold and Silver Pool Hospital, the statement is no longer as nervous as the first time. He will accompany patients to the end of the corridor, and then in the AIDS clinic at the door waiting for treatment and medicine.

Three or four times later, the statement could even tell those who had been stranded in Wuhan because of the siege, "walk down this corridor to the end, and the last one is the clinic, where you can pick up medicine. "

As a result of the impact of the epidemic, AIDS clinic doctors continue to improve efficiency. Some routine combinations of first-line and second-line drugs can be obtained directly in the outpatient clinic. Special Drugs require a doctor's prescription and take longer. But it's usually within 15 to 20 minutes for each a friend to get a week to half a month's worth of medication.

Most of the time, the statement carried three a-friends to the hospital. That day, there are five or six local Wuhan a friend also in the outpatient clinic and medicine. Stating that he had been waiting outside the hospital for over an hour.

In order to avoid flying droplets of infection, usually a friends in the car is not too much talk. On the contrary, after seeing out-patient clinic, after getting medicine, on the one hand to wait for other people, on the other hand to get a week or half a month of medicine supply after the mood is also a little bit relaxed, we will stand in a relatively empty place to chat.

"Are you infected, too? " Almost every a-friend would ask and declare.

"I am not. " The statement honest answer, but he believed that for a friend's care, should not only come from a friend itself, AIDS is only a chronic disease, "everyone is ordinary. "

"I deleted you. "

The epidemic situation, the closure of the city, became the pressure in the hearts of Wuhan people on the Boulder. For a friend, and more than others the same: AIDS, drug withdrawal. Many stay in Wuhan a friend, even if the local people, also often do not sleep well at night, the mind always like something. Perhaps he made it clear that he didn't want to stay at home and endure the invisible pressure of being shut down. Maybe he felt that being busy would make people feel more relaxed.

On Feb. 1, Wuhan, which had been sealed off for 10 days, was even quieter and more miserable, according to a statement that said more than a dozen a friends had been picked up for medication. Past Hankou's Jiefang Avenue, there are few lights, except for the sign on the side of the road that says "Go Wuhan" . The most bustling Wuguang shopping mall only left a billboard still lit up, the rest of the place a dim. The Unlit 2020 decoration of the Wu Guang building, which had been decorated on the eve of the New Year, was a beautiful exterior light, which now seemed to have been ripped off its coat and stood alone in the cold and overcast weather.

On This Day, it was stated that the most recent assignment from the community organization was to pick up and drop off an unusually quiet a friend. Wearing goggles and a mask, wearing a protective suit, he said little and sat in the back row in silence. By the time a friend got his medicine and went home, everyone else would have been more relaxed, but he was still extremely nervous.

In the pick-up and drop-off a friend in the process of medicine, the statement will not take the initiative to ask the name of the other party, will not inquire about their home address. Once, the declaration arrived at the gate of the community designated by a friend, waiting for nearly 20 minutes, the other side just dawdle to come out. From that time on, the statement will take the initiative to add to pick up a friend's Wechat, to avoid missing. After all, as one volunteer driver put it, "we risked our lives coming out here. "

When he got home and announced that he was cooking, the unusually silent a friend suddenly contacted him to announce that he had said a lot of polite words of thanks, and that he didn't understand what he was saying. "I deleted you. "

To state that he feels aggrieved. Although he didn't volunteer to make others appreciate him, the lack of trust made his trip seem ridiculous today. "maybe he can't accept that he has HIV, and he doesn't want strangers like me to know that he's an a-friend. " Even if no one else does anything, it's a potential threat to a-friend, who is terrified.

Stating that he didn't tell his would-be boyfriend about volunteering. These days, boyfriends and family members are hospitalized. "He seldom looks at his mobile phone, and most of the time we are the place where we have arranged to meet on Wechat, " the statement said, "This time, I can only accompany him on Wechat. I dare not tell him too much bad news, for fear that he will be more stressed. Every day I send him the number of people who have been cured and some encouraging videos I see. "

At first he had a fever and cough and wasn't feeling well. He couldn't answer more than three or five messages a day. By the end of January, he was well enough to "get used to chatting with me on Wechat, " he said. "It's sort of the epidemic that has changed the way we interact. "

It wasn't until Feb. 3, when the prospective boyfriend was released from the hospital, that he was told to volunteer.

"Do you want me to pick you up? You go to the hospital, you did not let me to send. " would-be boyfriend refused, "now you peace of mind to help others. "

I want to stay in the city

With the closure of the city, all districts of Wuhan were gradually closed. You need a pass to drive between zones. On February 4th, he was supposed to pick up and drop off two of his "a" friends. To his surprise, the first a friend was an old man over fifty, sitting in the back row. The second friend, also over 50, saw someone in the back row and sat in the front row.

I admire them, "people of this age are not native to Wuhan and do not speak Mandarin, but they can go around a lot through the community organization in their place of residence to reach out to people working in wuhan-related communities. "

Two elderly a friends kept saying thank you to the statement all the way, sitting in the front row of the old man also took out a pack of cigarettes, to give the statement. I declined the offer. When the two elderly in the statement to help with Mandarin "translation" under, respectively opened a good drug, and coincidentally stood at the gate of the Golden Pool Hospital, the first time to help them one by one call to thank the caring people. The statement was moved by the two old men. "Many elderly people and people who are not familiar with the Internet are most likely to be overlooked in an epidemic because they can not speak out. These two elderly people, although they do not know each other, can see that they are really pushed this time. "

Compared with the politeness of older friends, most of them were in their 20s, and even 20-year-old children. The child asked to be added to wechat after declaring that he would take him home. On February 5, the child suddenly contacted and declared, "I have quarreled with my family. Can you take me out? " The statement was very surprised, "What's the matter with you? Don't come out at this time, the family will be worried. " But the child kept contacting him for several days to make a statement, it means I want to stay with him. Finally, the statement was forced to keep silent.

Sometimes, declarations can be tiring when they get home. He's dying to get some rest. But the next day to receive a job, will still wear protective clothing out. "I heard that if the camera catches a private car driving outside now, it may be penalized in the future, right? " The statement said. "It's all news from everyone. But I think I've been out driving for so many days anyway, so I'll just keep picking up and dropping off a-friends. "

February 8, until after 9:00 at night, the declaration was busy back home. The Pot on the kitchen counter, still filled with boiling water from the morning before going out, was now cold. He re-lit the fire, although it is the Lantern Festival, want to make their own dumplings, but came back too late, too hungry, finally under the noodles. It was the first time he had not eaten Yuanxiao on the Lantern Festival.

There's still something to be happy about. That day, the statement sent to the boyfriend-to-be a mask and a consignment of prescribed drugs. The two men met a few hundred meters from the gate of the community. Although only a few minutes of time, the declaration also busy to pick up other a friends, but to see the boyfriend discharged in good spirits, the mood of the declaration a lot more relaxed.

In February, each time he passed by the Yangtze River, he couldn't help but look at it. The river still surges through the city, and Yellow Crane Tower stands silently on its banks, gazing at Wuhan, a city of more than 10 million people. These days, the statement of a friend shuttles around more and more to Wuhan three towns of huge and complex have a profound understanding. Although the landscape lights on the Yangtze River Bridge have been turned off, the lights on the road are still on.

Shen is not a sentimental person, but the silence in Wuhan these days makes him feel that the city seems to be dormant. "I grew up in Zhejiang and went to university in Fujian, " Shen said, "When I first came to Wuhan to work, I didn't really get used to seeing people slamming bus doors and fighting on the subway. I felt that the city was really too raw, and that it was very rude. "

But when the epidemic came, for various reasons, he declared that he chose to stay here and became a caring volunteer who picked up and dropped off friends A, "I want to stay in the city, and when the epidemic is over, maybe I'll buy a house and put down roots here, " he said. "I'll stick with it until I'm no longer needed. It's better if I'm no longer needed. "
